article.story: BOZEMAN, Mont. -- — Max Agbonkpolo and Jabe Mullins scored 14 points apiece in Montana State's 85-59 win against Abilene Christian on Tuesday. Agbonkpolo added seven rebounds and Mullins had seven assists for the Bobcats (3-4). Brandon Walker added 12 points and nine rebounds. The Wildcats (4-3) were led in scoring by Leonardo Bettiol, who finished with 18 points. Abilene Christian also got 10 points from Quion Williams. Rich Smith also had six points and six rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
